<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Political Parties</title>

    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 20px;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea, #764ba2);
      }

      h2 {
        text-align: center;
        color: white;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
      }

      .container {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
        gap: 20px;
      }

      .card {
        background: white;
        border-radius: 12px;
        padding: 20px;
        box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        transition: 0.3s;
      }

      .card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-5px);
      }

      .card img {
        width: 100px;
        height: 100px;
        object-fit: contain;
        display: block;
        margin: 0 auto 15px;
      }

      .card h3 {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }

      .card p {
        font-size: 14px;
        color: #444;
        text-align: justify;
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <h2>Major Political Parties of India</h2>

    <div class="container">
      <!-- AAP -->
      <div class="card">
        <img
          src="data:image/jpeg;base64,"
          alt="AAP Logo"
        />
        <h3>Aam Aadmi Party (AAP)</h3>
        <p>
          Aam Aadmi Party was founded in 2012 by Arvind Kejriwal. It focuses on
          anti-corruption, governance reforms, and public welfare policies. The
          party currently governs Delhi and Punjab.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- BJP -->
      <div class="card">
        <img
          src="data:image/png;base64,"
          alt="BJP Logo"
        />
        <h3>Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP)</h3>
        <p>
          BJP was founded in 1980 and is currently one of the largest political
          parties in India. It follows a nationalist ideology and is led at the
          national level by Prime Minister Narendra Modi.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- INC -->
      <div class="card">
        <img
          src="data:image/jpeg;base64,"
          alt="INC Logo"
        />
        <h3>Indian National Congress (INC)</h3>
        <p>
          Founded in 1885, the Indian National Congress played a major role in
          India's independence movement. It has historically been one of the two
          dominant political parties in India.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Samajwadi Party -->
      <div class="card">
        <img
          src="data:image/png;base64,"
          alt="SP Logo"
        />
        <h3>Samajwadi Party</h3>
        <p>
          Samajwadi Party was founded in 1992 and primarily operates in Uttar
          Pradesh. It promotes socialist policies and focuses on social justice
          and minority welfare.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
